Privacy Policy
Effective Date: March 31, 2026
App Name: Solitaire Master: Card Games
Package: com.solitairemaster.app

1. Introduction
Welcome to Solitaire Master: Card Games ("we," "our," or "us"). This Privacy Policy explains how we handle information when you use our mobile application. We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our practices.

2. Information We Collect
Solitaire Master: Card Games does not collect, store, or transmit any personal information.

All data generated by the app — including your game progress, statistics, achievements, settings, and preferences — is stored locally on your device only and never leaves your device.

Specifically, the app stores locally:

Game statistics (wins, losses, streaks, scores, times)
Achievement progress
Theme and customization preferences
Gameplay settings (sound, vibration, animation speed, etc.)
Daily challenge history
Coin and experience points balance
3. Information We Do NOT Collect
We do not collect:

Your name, email address, or any contact information
Device identifiers (IMEI, advertising ID, etc.)
Location data
Camera or microphone data
Contacts or calendar data
Browsing history or usage data sent to external servers
Financial or payment information
4. Internet Access
Solitaire Master: Card Games does not require an internet connection. The app does not connect to any servers, does not send any data over the internet, and does not communicate with any third parties.

5. Third-Party Services
This app does not integrate any third-party SDKs, analytics services, advertising networks, or social media platforms. No third party has access to any data related to your use of this app.

6. Children's Privacy
This app is suitable for all ages. Since we do not collect any personal information from any users, there is no risk to children's privacy. We comply with the Children's Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA) and similar regulations.

7. Data Storage and Security
All app data is stored locally on your device using Android's secure storage mechanisms (Room Database and DataStore). This data is protected by your device's built-in security. Uninstalling the app will permanently delete all locally stored data.

8. Your Rights
Since we do not collect or store any personal data on external servers, there is no personal data for us to provide, correct, or delete on our end. If you wish to reset all app data, you can:

Clear the app's data via Android Settings → Apps → Solitaire Master: Card Games → Clear Data
Uninstall the app
9. Permissions
The app requests only the following permission:

VIBRATE — Used solely to provide haptic feedback during gameplay when you enable the vibration setting. No data is collected through this permission.
